From: ram <chan2006@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 16:42:54 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Auto-detect Azure subscription instead of requiring manual
 entry
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Since the customer already has to copy their Subscription ID once
to do the Reader role assignment in Azure Portal, requiring them to
type/paste it a second time into ArchAI was redundant friction.

- app/api/azure-connect/list-subscriptions: new route. Calls ARM's
  /subscriptions endpoint with the app-only token — this only
  returns results once Reader has actually been assigned somewhere
  (an empty result is expected and normal before that step, not an
  error).
- components/brownfield/BrownfieldClient.tsx: automatically calls
  this once the RBAC step is reached. If exactly one subscription
  is detected, auto-fills and shows it confirmed; if multiple, shows
  a dropdown to pick from; if none yet (RBAC not done/propagated),
  falls back to manual entry with a 'check again' button rather
  than blocking on it. Fixed a set-state-in-effect lint issue via
  the same queueMicrotask pattern used earlier, and an unescaped
  apostrophe.

Verified: tsc --noEmit clean, next build succeeds (new
list-subscriptions route confirmed), no new lint errors beyond the
one pre-existing no-html-link-for-pages issue.
